<figureCitation id="E3EA2A12FFA8FFE85AD4FA7DE6B0FA2D" box="[461,508,1475,1499]" captionStart="Figure 134-139" captionStartId="52.[195,279,1749,1771]" captionTargetBox="[265,1366,242,1648]" captionTargetId="figure-18@52.[250,1381,195,1703]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figure 134-139. Male genitalia of Porphyrogenes; shown are lateral view of uncus, gnathos, tegumen, and saccus; dorsal view of uncus and tegumen; ventral view of uncus and gnathos; juxta; lateral view (with extended vesica) and often dorsal view of aedeagus; internal lateral view of right valva (inset shows the flattened harpe). 134) P. boliva, BRAZIL: Rondônia (GTA 3499); 135) P. ferruginea, BRAZIL: Amazonas (GTA 4184); 136) P. despecta, BRAZIL:Pará (GTA 7587); 137) P. omphale, BRAZIL: Rondônia (GTA 3229); 138) P. pausias, BRAZIL: Rondônia (GTA 4212); 139) P. probus, BRAZIL: Rondônia (GTA 6700)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5169720" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5169720/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">138</figureCitation>
